The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 September is 3,190 (369.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 September, there were 139 new confirmed cases (16.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 September, there were 94 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 48% (45 extra cases).
